  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Recovering from Conflict: Integrated Support for Most Vulnerable Communities in South Kordofan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This programme is designed to address insecurities of vulnerable communities in South Kordofan State of Sudan, who were most severely affected by the conflicts and following mass displacement and large numbers of returnees. The programme takes a multi-sectoral and community-based approach to strengthen access to basic services and water and sanitation hygiene, livelihood systems, education, and protection measures following the successful clearing landmines and explosive remnants of war in and around the community. The effectiveness and sustainability of the programme is enhanced by adopting and mainstreaming the human security approach, which aims to advance protection and empowerment strategies and responses that are people-centered, context-specific, comprehensive, and prevention-oriented.</narrative>
  </description>
